===Pronunciation===
* [[IPA]]: /ˈæspɻɪn/

===Etymology===
From the German trademark ''Aspirin''.  The word is still used as a trademark in some countries, but has entered the language in common usage in the US and the UK.

===Noun===
'''aspirin'''

# an [[analgesic]] [[drug]], acetylsalicylic acid.

